9kgp is 12 Wands of CLW, for 3300hp cured and no spell slots used
(twice that with Lesser Vigor). You'll be casting scores of spells to
get the same total effect, oh, and the rod only works 3/day so it's
likely taking your entire career to make up the cost difference. Plus,
someone with the wands gets to use those few spells each day for
something else, like another 1000hp healing or more over the levels.
A wand user doesn't have to bother with Augment Healing, and can
share them around.

Sudden costs a feat for 1/day. *Never* worth it when you could
take &quot;Extra Slot&quot; and cast another /Heal/ spell. With the regular feat
you're better to just use the higher level Vigor spells.

Either way, it takes 20 minutes to get the 42 hp each, and no
speeding it up, so to heal up a damaged high level party would take
*hours*, and you still need quicker healing available for emergencies.

Overall, I call it a munchkin trap, and not a very good one.

